The paper presents a face detection approach that involves using a 3D model to represent the spatial relationship between face parts. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes using image-based regression and a parameter sensitive classifier, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves evaluating the proposed approach on face detection datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper addresses the computational complexity of the approach, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
